description:
Attractive art deco hotel next to Paddington Station

Upscale shopping
Next to the train station of the same name, Hilton London Paddington puts you within walking distance of Hyde Park and the high-end boutiques that line Oxford Street. For everything under one roof, Whiteleys shopping center is just a 15-minute walk.

Royal attractions
This hotel is steps from London Paddington and less than 10 minutes from Lancaster Gate Tube Station. You can take a 15-minute stroll to Kensington Palace and Gardens, or hop on the Tube to reach Buckingham Palace in just a few stops.

Chic dining
This smoke-free Hilton offers an elegant fine dining experience at Brasserie restaurant. Hip bar Steam features late night dining and nightcaps in a chic setting that is perfect for entertaining. If you have any steam left, you can let it off in the fully equipped fitness center open around the clock. Business amenities include 18 meeting rooms and free WiFi in public areas. Limo or town car service are also available, as well as onsite shopping.

Luxury living
Guestrooms feature WiFi and flat-screen TVs with satellite channels and pay movies. Spacious rooms with large windows help enhance the art deco style. Designer toiletries and marble bathrooms add a touch of glamour and luxury to the rooms.

HOTEL_AMENITY.value:
At Hilton London Paddington's fully-serviced business center, guests have access (on a first-come, first-served basis) to 2 PCs with high-speed Internet access, a printer, fax, scanner, and photocopier (fees apply). Free WiFi is available in public areas. Secretarial services are also available during office hours for a fee. The hotel also offers 18 versatile meeting rooms. For those wishing to keep fit, the hotel offers a well-equipped fitness center with the latest cardiovascular equipment. Towels, showers and mineral water are provided. Full meals and refreshments are available from the stylish Brasserie restaurant, a discreet lounge-bar, and the contemporary Steam Bar.

Parking is not available on site, but is available nearby for a surcharge. Limo or town car are also available, as well as onsite shops. This property is smoke-free.

DINING.value:
The Brasserie - Chic and contemporary, this two-level restaurant features polished wood floors, steel lamps with frosted-glass shades, a humidor, and bar. Upholstered chairs and banquettes surround tables topped with crisp white linens and fresh flowers. Serves modern international cuisine for lunch and dinner and a hot and cold buffet breakfast.

The Lounge - Nestled beneath the lobby's sweeping staircase, the Lounge is a dimly lit, discreet venue in which to enjoy pastries, sandwiches, afternoon tea, or a drink. Relaxing in armchairs and sofas, guests are serenaded by the grand player-piano.

Steam - A destination bar, Steam is big, bright, and boldly designed. Huge black-and-white photos are mounted on exposed brickwork walls, and ceiling lights hang over multi-colored bar stools, armchairs, and tables. Hotel guests and Londoners heading for a night on the town talk above the not-too-loud rock music and choose from an extensive range of wines, beer, cocktails, and light international dishes.



Please check the Rooms and Rates page to see which rates include breakfast.
